******************Map layout***********************
1.	Switch to Map Layout: 
  1)	Go to Layout View by clicking bottom left of map.
  2)	Change orientation: File menu -> Page and Print Setup, then click Landscape and Scale Map.
  3)	Right-click map to Distribute -> Fit to Margins, and then click Full Extent
2.	Adding Map Title:
  1)	From Insert drop-down menu, click Title
  2)	When prompted, insert space. Then double click on text block and type title. Title must include unit of geography, where and year.
  3)	Resize map by dragging corners to fit title
  4)	To edit, double click again: enter a <return> to separate lines of text if needed; click Change Symbol to edit font size.
3.	Adding Map Legend: remember the missing data
  1)	From Insert drop-down menu, click Legend
  2)	Use arrows to move layers to and from legend
  3)	Delete ‘Legend’ from legend title. Next to continue.
  4)	Once created, double click for Legend Properties
  5)	Click Select All, then Style button; use 1st style in 3rd row: Horizontal Single, Layer Name, and Label
  6)	Select second layer and check button to place in new column
  7)	Click Select All, then Font: Click Symbol and use dropdown menu to select font size: headings = 18; class labels=16. Both bold.
  8)	Double click legend and click Layout tab. Change column gap to 20. Move Legend to below map.
4.	Other map elements:
  1)	From Insert drop-down menu, click North Arrow and select a style. Change size by expanding box.
  2)	From Insert drop-down menu, click Scale Bar and select a style. Double click on scale bar to change units and number of divisions. Scale Bar must go beneath map.
  3)	Left-click map to select, then right click to open Properties. Click Frame tab and select no border. Can also change background color.
  4)	From File drop-down menu, go to Export Map.

*****************Multiple Maps in a Layout**************************
  1)	Insert a New Data Frame from the Insert drop-down menu. Drag the Multiple Race and Urban and High Poverty layers to the new data frame.
  2)	Use Size and Position in Data Frame Properties to resize and reposition. Click Full Extent to enlarge map to fit frame. Eg: Position: X: 5.5 inch, Y: 0; Size: Width: 5.5 inch, Height: 7.3 inch. 
  3)	Convert to Graphics > Ungroup > to edit legend: Note make sure you correct the dot number (1 Dot = 1)
 
